\par \pard\plain \s38\sa120\nowidctlpar \f4\lang2057 To configure the Java interface in {\i Pow!}, either create a new Project using a Java template or open an existing Java project. Select \ldblquote Options\rdblquote  and then \ldblquote Directories
\rdblquote  in the menu bar.
\par In the field {\b Class path }you have to enter a list of locations where the compiler should search for classes. This might look like \ldblquote .; c:\\jdk1.2\\jre\\lib\\rt.jar\rdblquote .
\par In the field {\b JDK home} you have to specify the path to the JDK binaries directory. This might look like \ldblquote c:\\jdk1.2\\bin\rdblquote .
\par You have to change the system search path to include the binaries directory of your JDK installation.
\par \pard\plain \s34\qj\sb240\sa120\keepn\nowidctlpar \b\f4\fs32\lang2057 \page {\cs19\fs16\up6 #{\footnote \pard\plain \s20\qj\sa120\nowidctlpar \f4\fs20\lang1031 {\cs19\fs16\up6 #}{\fs16  GeneralIntroduction}}${\footnote \pard\plain 
